contentrichtext.text: '''Young Communist League of Sweden''' (''Sveriges Kommunistiska UngdomsfÃ¶rbund'') is the a name used by three separate organizations in [[Sweden]]: * It was the name of the organization presently known as [[Young Left (Sweden)|Young Left]] 1921-1958. * In 1977, [[Arbetarpartiet Kommunisterna|APK]] founded a youth wing called [[Young Communist League of Sweden (1977)|SKU]]. * In 2000, [[Communist Party of Sweden (1995)|SKP]] (the successor of APK) founded a youth wing called [[Young Communist League of Sweden (2000)|SKU]]. {{Disambiguation}}
